In our lab we arranged resistors of different values in series. We found current by dividing
total voltage by total resistance. Power was found by multiplying voltage and current. Total resistance
with all serial resistors meant we just added all the resistance values together. Deviation was found by
Dev=(It-Im/It)*100. We were able to get our actual voltage source to 10.00V so we used 10V for our
calculations and measurements. We used 1kΩ, 2.3kΩ, 3.9kΩ instead of 3.3kΩ since we could not find
one, and 6.8kΩ resistors for this lab.
